  "prompt": "How do I swim?",
  "response": "Swimming is a valuable skill that combines technique, practice, and confidence. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you get started:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Get Comfortable in the Water**\n- Start in shallow water where you can stand comfortably.\n- Practice floating on your back to get used to the water supporting your body.\n- Submerge your face in the water and practice controlled breathing (exhale through your nose or mouth underwater, inhale when your face is above water).\n\n---\n\n### **2. Learn Basic Floating**\n- **Back Float:** Lean back, spread your arms and legs slightly, and let the water support your body. Keep your head back and lift your chin slightly.\n- **Front Float:** Hold your breath, place your face in the water, and stretch your body out horizontally. Use your arms and legs to balance.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Practice Kicking**\n- Hold onto the edge of the pool or use a kickboard.\n- Keep your legs straight with slightly pointed toes and kick from your hips, not your knees.\n- Practice flutter kicks (alternating up-and-down leg movements) for freestyle or breaststroke kicks (frog-like motion).\n\n---\n\n### **4. Master Arm Movements**\n- **Freestyle:** Alternate your arms in a windmill motion. Reach forward, pull the water back, and recover by lifting your arm out of the water.\n- **Breaststroke:** Move your arms in a circular motion, pushing the water outward and then bringing your hands together in front of your chest.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Combine Breathing with Strokes**\n- Turn your head to the side during freestyle to breathe. Exhale underwater and inhale when your face is turned.\n- For breaststroke, lift your head slightly to breathe as your arms pull back.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Practice Coordination**\n- Combine your kicks, arm movements, and breathing into smooth, fluid motions.\n- Start slowly and focus on proper technique before increasing speed.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Build Confidence and Endurance**\n- Swim short distances at first, gradually increasing as you become more comfortable.\n- Practice regularly to improve strength, coordination, and stamina.\n\n---\n\n### **Safety Tips**\n- Always swim in a safe environment, preferably with a lifeguard present.\n- Never swim alone; have a buddy or supervision.\n- Learn basic water safety and rescue techniques.\n\n---\n\nIf you\u2019re a beginner, consider taking lessons from a certified swimming instructor to ensure you learn proper techniques and stay safe. With practice and patience, you\u2019ll soon be swimming confidently!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
